Addon.name: Tiny Blocks addon
Addon.role: Shrink the blocks in size a few times in a matter of seconds using the Tiny Blocks addon. And just like that, you'll receive an unlimited creation tool for decorations. Make a smaller cake and put it on the table, just to sit there and look nice. Create a shop window with tiny items displayed on it - be creative. Around 240 small blocks will be disposable to you.

Among the items that have a chance to drop are diamond tools and armor, iron tools, wool, villager, creeper, explosion, enchanted armor, etc.

Destroy the block underneath you to get the new one - sometimes you will get the chest, and sometimes a monster. Develop your island, home, and farm resources. The ultimate goal of the one block survival is to make a way into the End and kill a dragon in MCPE. If you'd like the map, check out the random skyblock map too.

Map.name: Ultimate Skyblock map
Map.role: What makes this Skyblock special is that it features a small-sized economy in it. Just like any other Skyblock, it starts on an island, but now you need to produce resources and trade them for currency. Grow crops, sell them for money and then buy the things that you need to grow your production and economy. So it's more like a capitalist survival than a regular Skyblock.

Map.name: Enhanced Biomes Addon
Map.role: From time to time, you need to update the appearance of Minecraft Bedrock so that the game does not bother. But typical tools are sometimes not enough, and standard texture packages and shaders do not give the desired effect. In this case, try the Enhanced Biomes addon! After installing it, each biome in the MCPE game will become better. The spawn of hills, trees, villages and other elements will change and become cooler! The player will have a greater chance of stumbling into hidden, atmospheric villages. And biome landscapes will bewitch the views. In addition, this addon contains shaders that will change the lighting and elaboration of the game world. If you look at the screenshot of Hell, you will understand how much the lighting will change.

Map.name: Tower Parkour map for Minecraft PE 1.16.1
Map.role: Parkour maps have become all-time classics in Minecraft, and this map is just an example of how good it can be to jump in a game. The one thing that distinguishes this map from the other is that all parkour stuff is happening in the area of the 5x5 blocks. Limites is what makes the map harder to beat. By the end of your playthrough, you will be damning those corners, which will become the main reason for falling.

Map.name: Skyblock islands map for Minecraft PE 1.16.200

The main thing that makes the difference between this and the other maps of this kind is the additional islands that float around and creates possibilities for further development of your survival. Your main goals will be: to build a home, have enough food, expand the main island, and reach the other ones.

Suggestions are appreciated, the map is still in beta.
